  "prompt": "Which songs are best for shrilled voice?",
  "response": "Songs suited for a shrilled voice typically have higher vocal ranges and can showcase the brightness and clarity of the voice. Here\u2019s a list of songs across various genres that work well for a shrilled voice:\n\n### Pop:\n1. **\"Rolling in the Deep\"** - Adele  \n   (High-energy with powerful high notes.)  \n2. **\"Chandelier\"** - Sia  \n   (Challenges the upper range with emotional intensity.)  \n3. **\"Firework\"** - Katy Perry  \n   (Uplifting chorus with high-pitched vocals.)  \n4. **\"Stay\"** - Rihanna  \n   (Emotional and featuring sustained high notes.)  \n\n### Rock:\n5. **\"Somebody to Love\"** - Queen (Freddie Mercury)  \n   (Classic rock with soaring high notes.)  \n6. **\"Barracuda\"** - Heart (Ann Wilson)  \n   (Powerful and high-pitched.)  \n7. **\"Crazy on You\"** - Heart  \n   (Showcases both range and intensity.)  \n\n### Classical/Opera:\n8. **\"O mio babbino caro\"** - Giacomo Puccini  \n   (Beautiful aria for a soprano voice.)  \n9. **\"Queen of the Night Aria\"** - Mozart (from *The Magic Flute*)  \n   (Extremely high-pitched and challenging.)  \n10. **\"Ave Maria\"** - Franz Schubert  \n    (Elegant and showcases vocal clarity.)  \n\n### Musical Theater:\n11. **\"Defying Gravity\"** - *Wicked* (Idina Menzel)  \n    (Powerful and high-reaching notes.)  \n12. **\"Tomorrow\"** - *Annie*  \n    (Bright and cheerful, suited for a youthful shrilled voice.)  \n13. **\"Think of Me\"** - *The Phantom of the Opera*  \n    (Classic soprano piece with soaring notes.)  \n\n### R&B/Soul:\n14. **\"I Will Always Love You\"** - Whitney Houston  \n    (Iconic high notes and emotional depth.)  \n15. **\"If I Ain\u2019t Got You\"** - Alicia Keys  \n    (Versatile with opportunities to hit high notes.)  \n\n### Indie/Alternative:\n16. **\"Dog Days Are Over\"** - Florence + The Machine  \n    (Upbeat with a high-pitched, energetic chorus.)  \n17. **\"Skinny Love\"** - Birdy (or Bon Iver version)  \n    (Emotional and soft, yet high-pitched.)  \n\n### Bollywood (for those interested in Indian music):\n18. **\"Radha\"** - *Student of the Year* (Shreya Ghoshal)  \n    (High-pitched and melodious.)  \n19. **\"Deewani Mastani\"** - *Bajirao Mastani*  \n    (Ornate and soprano-friendly.)  \n\n### K-Pop:\n20. **\"Into the New World\"** - Girls\u2019 Generation  \n    (Bright and high-pitched, perfect for a shrilled voice.)  \n\nThese songs allow a shrilled voice to shine by highlighting its clarity, brightness, and ability to hit higher notes. However, it\u2019s important to choose songs that feel comfortable and suit your unique vocal style!",
